Source77NW glossary - LSV sample data for the Lookup sample.
This preamble is free space: everything before the first record
marker is ignored by the parser. The convention:

  :<recordCode> <name/values>    begins a record
  .<fieldName> <value>           begins a named field
  unmarked lines                 continue the field's value

Fields are optional and repeatable per record; multi-line values
need no escaping. Lookup indexes ':def' records by name; other
record codes (':rem' remarks, ':::' dividers) are skipped.

:GLOSSARY Source77NW terms
.what sample data for samples/Lookup

:rem A remark record - Lookup's record-code filter skips this, the
same way Cmd.OpsUser skips REM records in an OPS document.

:def LOUD
.desc Contract violations throw an Issue immediately - misuse of
the library is never absorbed.
.ant SOFT
.note The Issue regime is the LOUD channel: raise with a distinct
Spot, dispatch by Kind at the boundary that can respond.

:def SOFT
.desc Absence is a state, not an error: Try*/Got*/Did* surfaces
report a miss with bool + out instead of throwing.
.ant LOUD
.note The method name tells you the miss behavior - Got/Plucked
return false, *_or_null returns null, *_or_NUL returns '\0'.

:def Pluck
.desc Consume from the bottom of a view or stack.
.ant Pop
.note Chars plucks chars, tokens, digits, and lines from the view
bottom; ItemStack.Pluck() takes the oldest item (FIFO).

:def Pop
.desc Consume from the top of a view or stack.
.ant Pluck
.note ItemStack.Pop() takes the newest item (LIFO); the same stack
serves both orders, which is the whole trick of samples/Inspect.

::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::

:def Chars
.desc A struct view (BotIndex, TopIndex) over one base string;
scanning and parsing move the bounds - no substrings are created.
.note Compares by content, so views over DIFFERENT base strings
sort and search together - see samples/Lookup itself.
.note Write(TextWriter) streams the view out: even output needs
no ToString.

:def ItemStack
.desc A sliding-window stack that is also a cheap queue: Push, Pop
(LIFO), Pluck (FIFO), Sort, BinarySearch - a bare-metal core.
.note Single-threaded, lock-free, loud on misuse; StackAgent is
the wrapping Agent when exposure needs guarding.

:def Issue
.desc The single application exception: Kind + Source + Spot pack
into HResult; handling dispatches on Kind, not on exception type.
.note Core tiers reserve issueSource 65,000+; samples and apps use
the low range.

:def Spot
.desc A byte pinning the exact raise site within a module's
issueSource number.

:def ARHSCE
.desc FileAttr's six-char dot format: Archive ReadOnly Hidden
System Compressed Encrypted.

:def LSV
.desc Line Separated Values: ':' begins a record (record code
first), '.' begins a named field, and unmarked lines continue the
field's value.
.note The markers are positional, so the only restriction on value
text is that a line may not BEGIN with ':' or '.'; multi-line
values therefore need no escaping - the format's founding trick.

:def Agent
.desc The wrapping layer that adds locking, async, and validation
around a bare-metal core (StackAgent around ItemStack).
.ant Core
